abstract: This play depicts the scabrous wit of a woman and a man who get to know each other when their cancer-afflicted mothers share a hospital room.
snippet: This play depicts the scabrous wit of a woman and a man who get to know each other when their cancer-afflicted mothers share a hospital room.
lead_paragraph: There’s a raw spot — one of the tenderest places on the continent of human emotions — that exists between laughter and pain. Make that between laughter and everything that feeds pain: rage, hatred, desperation, hopelessness, fear, even physical disease.

abstract: His prodigies want to rewire the world. Will that mean more than inventing the next Snapchat?
snippet: His prodigies want to rewire the world. Will that mean more than inventing the next Snapchat?
lead_paragraph: THE battle between Gawker and the tech titan Peter Thiel has made him look like a spiteful manipulator with a bully wallet. But this characterization is incomplete. The stakes and ambitions of Mr. Thiel’s back-room lawsuit-jiggering are fairly trivial compared with many of his endeavors — some stealthy, some gleefully public — to rewire the world to his liking.

abstract: The power of money in politics is being felt ever deeper down the ballot.
snippet: The power of money in politics is being felt ever deeper down the ballot.
lead_paragraph: Like practiced horseplayers at a racetrack, wealthy campaign donors are adjusting their bets as the primary season ends and the political field narrows. This is particularly true of Republican megadonors who cannot abide Donald Trump and are thus doubling down on keeping G.O.P. control of the Senate as a firewall against a possible Democratic president, while investing heavily in keeping statehouses in Republican hands.

abstract: Limit the number of “gut feeling” jury strikes to just one or two per side.
snippet: Limit the number of “gut feeling” jury strikes to just one or two per side.
lead_paragraph: THE Supreme Court ruled correctly on Monday when it found that Georgia prosecutors in Foster v. Chatman had illegally barred African-Americans from serving as jurors in a death penalty trial. But the decision does not end racial discrimination in jury selection. The best way to do that is to limit the number of jurors that lawyers can strike for no reason at all to just one or two per side.

abstract: The truck, whose architecture has remained mostly the same since its inception in 1979, is a combination of luxury, utility, capability and status.
snippet: The truck, whose architecture has remained mostly the same since its inception in 1979, is a combination of luxury, utility, capability and status.
lead_paragraph: MERCEDES-BENZ makes vehicles with cutting-edge design. The G550 isn’t one of them, and that gives it a war horse appeal. With an architecture that has remained much the same since its inception in 1979, the G-Class, also known as the Gelandewagen, could be the touchstone that spawned the phrase “old school.”

abstract: The reshuffling in fashion executive suites is nearly as dramatic as on the creative side.
snippet: The reshuffling in fashion executive suites is nearly as dramatic as on the creative side.
lead_paragraph: We tend to forget, in our obsession with designer moves , that upheaval in the executive suite is equally disruptive, and potentially meaningful, when it comes to reshaping the fashion we see and wear.

headline_main: Fashion Shake-Ups Go Beyond Designers to the C-Suite

abstract: Lawyers for New England quarterback Tom Brady want an expanded panel of judges to make the decision after a three-judge panel ruled in favor of Commissioner Roger Goodell.
snippet: Lawyers for New England quarterback Tom Brady want an expanded panel of judges to make the decision after a three-judge panel ruled in favor of Commissioner Roger Goodell.
lead_paragraph: Tom Brady’s lawyers asked a federal appeals court in New York for a new hearing before an expanded panel of judges, arguing on Monday that it was not just a silly dispute over underinflated footballs — it was the basic right to a fair process that was shared by all union workers.
